#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn10.8"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn10.8:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 10 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 10 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.8:0.2"
msgid "1. Indakavagga "
msgstr "1. With Indaka "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn10.8:0.3"
msgid "8. Sudattasutta "
msgstr "8. With Sudatta "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.211, pts2ed1.456, sc1
msgctxt "sn10.8:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati sītavane. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha in the Cool Grove. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.8:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati rājagahaṃ anuppatto hoti kenacideva karaṇīyena. "
msgstr "Now at that time the householder Anāthapiṇḍika had arrived at Rājagaha on some business. "

msgctxt "sn10.8:1.3"
msgid "Assosi kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati: "
msgstr "He heard "

msgctxt "sn10.8:1.4"
msgid "“buddho kira loke uppanno”ti. "
msgstr "a rumor that a Buddha had arisen in the world. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.8:1.5"
msgid "Tāvadeva ca pana bhagavantaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamitukāmo hoti. Athassa anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Right away he wanted to go and see the Buddha, but he thought, "

msgctxt "sn10.8:1.6"
msgid "“akālo kho ajja bhagavantaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ. "
msgstr "“It’s too late to go and see the Buddha today. "

msgctxt "sn10.8:1.7"
msgid "Sve dānāhaṃ kālena bhagavantaṃ dassanāya gamissāmī”ti buddhagatāya satiyā nipajji. "
msgstr "I’ll go and see him tomorrow.” He went to bed thinking of the Buddha. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.8:1.8"
msgid "Rattiyā sudaṃ tikkhattuṃ vuṭṭhāsi pabhātanti maññamāno. "
msgstr "During the night he got up three times thinking it was morning. "

#. VAR: sivathikadvāraṃ → sīvathikadvāraṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn10.8:1.9"
msgid "Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati yena sivathikadvāraṃ tenupasaṅkami. "
msgstr "Then he approached the Sivaka Gate, "

msgctxt "sn10.8:1.10"
msgid "Amanussā dvāraṃ vivariṃsu. "
msgstr "and non-human beings opened it for him. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.8:1.11"
msgid "Atha kho anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa nagaramhā nikkhamantassa āloko antaradhāyi, andhakāro pāturahosi, bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃso udapādi, tatova puna nivattitukāmo ahosi. "
msgstr "But as he was leaving the city, light vanished and darkness appeared to him. He felt fear, terror, and goosebumps, and wanted to turn back. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: sivako → sīvako (bj, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn10.8:1.12"
msgid "Atha kho sivako yakkho antarahito saddamanussāvesi: "
msgstr "Then the invisible spirit Sivaka called out: "

# NOTE: BB follows comm in expanding this to 100,000, but the Chinese parallels at SA 592 and SA2 186 prefer the more modest and literal figure of 100.
#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2, verse-num-sc837
msgctxt "sn10.8:2.1"
msgid "“Sataṃ hatthī sataṃ assā, "
msgstr "“A hundred elephants, a hundred horses, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:2.2"
msgid "Sataṃ assatarīrathā; "
msgstr "a hundred mule-drawn chariots, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:2.3"
msgid "Sataṃ kaññāsahassāni, "
msgstr "a hundred thousand maidens "

# NOTE: āmukka is a variant of āmutta.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:2.4"
msgid "Āmukkamaṇikuṇḍalā; "
msgstr "bedecked with jewels and earrings: "

# NOTE: BB’s “step” for padavitihara is incorrect, it is a special term denoting a “great stride forward” for which “stride” alone is barely adequate. He has adopted “stride” in AN.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:2.5"
msgid "Ekassa padavītihārassa, "
msgstr "these are not worth a sixteenth part "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:2.6"
msgid "Kalaṃ nāgghanti soḷasiṃ. "
msgstr "of a single forward stride! "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, verse-num-sc838
msgctxt "sn10.8:3.1"
msgid "Abhikkama gahapati, "
msgstr "Forward, householder! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:3.2"
msgid "abhikkama gahapati; "
msgstr "Forward, householder! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:3.3"
msgid "Abhikkamanaṃ te seyyo, "
msgstr "Going forward is better for you, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:3.4"
msgid "no paṭikkamanan”ti. "
msgstr "not turning back!” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn10.8:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa andhakāro antaradhāyi, āloko pāturahosi, yaṃ ahosi bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃso, so paṭippassambhi. "
msgstr "Then darkness vanished and light appeared to Anāthapiṇḍika. His fear, terror, and goosebumps settled down. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.8:4.2"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa āloko antaradhāyi, andhakāro pāturahosi, bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃso udapādi, tatova puna nivattitukāmo ahosi. "
msgstr "But for a second time, light vanished and darkness appeared to him. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.8:4.3"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho sivako yakkho antarahito saddamanussāvesi: "
msgstr "For a second time the invisible spirit Sivaka called out … "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc5, verse-num-sc839
msgctxt "sn10.8:5.1"
msgid "“Sataṃ hatthī sataṃ assā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:5.2"
msgid "… pe … "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:5.3"
msgid "Kalaṃ nāgghanti soḷasiṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.457, sc6
msgctxt "sn10.8:6.1"
msgid "Abhikkama gahapati, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:6.2"
msgid "abhikkama gahapati; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:6.3"
msgid "Abhikkamanaṃ te seyyo, "
msgstr "“… Going forward is better for you, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:6.4"
msgid "no paṭikkamanan”ti. "
msgstr "not turning back!” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.212, sc7
msgctxt "sn10.8:7.1"
msgid "Atha kho anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa andhakāro antaradhāyi, āloko pāturahosi, yaṃ ahosi bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃso, so paṭippassambhi. "
msgstr "Then darkness vanished and light appeared to Anāthapiṇḍika. His fear, terror, and goosebumps settled down. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.8:7.2"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa āloko antaradhāyi, andhakāro pāturahosi, bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃso udapādi, tatova puna nivattitukāmo ahosi. "
msgstr "But for a third time, light vanished and darkness appeared to him. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.8:7.3"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho sivako yakkho antarahito saddamanussāvesi: "
msgstr "For a third time the invisible spirit Sivaka called out … "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn10.8:8.1"
msgid "“Sataṃ hatthī sataṃ assā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:8.2"
msgid "… pe … "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:8.3"
msgid "Kalaṃ nāgghanti soḷasiṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn10.8:9.1"
msgid "Abhikkama gahapati, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:9.2"
msgid "abhikkama gahapati; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:9.3"
msgid "Abhikkamanaṃ te seyyo, "
msgstr "“… Going forward is better for you, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:9.4"
msgid "no paṭikkamanan”ti. "
msgstr "not turning back!” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn10.8:10.1"
msgid "Atha kho anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa andhakāro antaradhāyi, āloko pāturahosi, yaṃ ahosi bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃso, so paṭippassambhi. "
msgstr "Then darkness vanished and light appeared to Anāthapiṇḍika. His fear, terror, and goosebumps settled down. "

msgctxt "sn10.8:10.2"
msgid "Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati yena sītavanaṃ yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami. "
msgstr "Then the householder Anāthapiṇḍika went to the Cool Grove and approached the Buddha. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.458, sc11
msgctxt "sn10.8:11.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ paccuṭṭhāya abbhokāse caṅkamati. "
msgstr "Now at that time the Buddha had risen at the crack of dawn and was walking meditation in the open. "

msgctxt "sn10.8:11.2"
msgid "Addasā kho bhagavā anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ. "
msgstr "He saw Anāthapiṇḍika coming off in the distance. "

msgctxt "sn10.8:11.3"
msgid "Disvāna caṅkamā orohitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. "
msgstr "So he stepped down from the walking path, sat down on the seat spread out, "

msgctxt "sn10.8:11.4"
msgid "Nisajja kho bhagavā anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "and said to Anāthapiṇḍika, "

msgctxt "sn10.8:11.5"
msgid "“ehi, sudattā”ti. "
msgstr "“Come, Sudatta.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.8:11.6"
msgid "Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati, nāmena maṃ bhagavā ālapatīti, haṭṭho udaggo tattheva bhagavato pādesu sirasā nipatitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Anāthapiṇḍika thought, “The Buddha calls me by name!” Smiling and joyful, he bowed with his head to the Buddha’s feet and said to him, "

msgctxt "sn10.8:11.7"
msgid "“kacci, bhante, bhagavā sukhamasayitthā”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, I trust the Buddha slept well?” "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc12, verse-num-sc840
msgctxt "sn10.8:12.1"
msgid "“Sabbadā ve sukhaṃ seti, "
msgstr "“A brahmin who is fully extinguished "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:12.2"
msgid "brāhmaṇo parinibbuto; "
msgstr "always sleeps well. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:12.3"
msgid "Yo na limpati kāmesu, "
msgstr "Sensual pleasures slide off them, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:12.4"
msgid "sītibhūto nirūpadhi. "
msgstr "they’re cooled, free of attachments. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13, verse-num-sc841
msgctxt "sn10.8:13.1"
msgid "Sabbā āsattiyo chetvā, "
msgstr "Since they’ve cut off all clinging, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:13.2"
msgid "vineyya hadaye daraṃ; "
msgstr "and removed the stress from the heart, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:13.3"
msgid "Upasanto sukhaṃ seti, "
msgstr "the peaceful sleep well, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: cetasā”ti → cetasoti (bj, pts2)
msgctxt "sn10.8:13.4"
msgid "santiṃ pappuyya cetasā”ti. "
msgstr "abiding in peace of mind.”"

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
